data.database_description: The database tracks customer information, addresses, orders, and products. It maintains detailed records of customers' contact details, order history, and product purchases, with links between customers and their address history through foreign keys, enabling comprehensive management of customer relationships and transactions.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each address.
First line of the address, including street number and building name.
City part of the address.
Postal code or ZIP code for the address.
State, province, or county part of the address.
Country part of the address.

sample_data: 1, 4315 Kerluke Canyon Apt. 800, Hertafurt, 740, Nevada, USA
2, 319 Kozey Highway Suite 973, Edgardoberg, 282, Colorado, USA
enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores detailed address information for customers.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each product.
Type code categorizing the product (e.g., Hardware, Clothes).
Name of the product.
Price of the product.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about products available for purchase, including type, name, and price.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each customer.
Indicates the method of payment used by the customer (e.g., Credit Card, Direct Debit).
A unique number assigned to each customer.
The name of the customer.
The address where the customer is located.
The phone number associated with the customer.
The email address of the customer.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about customers, including their contact details and payment methods.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each contact record.
Foreign key linking the contact to a specific customer in the Customers table.
Gender of the contact, represented by a single character (M/F).
First name of the contact.
Last name of the contact.
Phone number for contacting the individual, including any extensions.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores detailed contact information for customers, including personal details and contact methods.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for the customer associated with the address.
Unique identifier for the address associated with the customer.
Start date when the customer was associated with this address.
End date when the customer stopped being associated with this address.
Unique identifier for each order.
Identifier linking the order to a specific customer.
Date and time when the order was placed.
Current status of the order (e.g., Completed, Part).

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores records of customer orders including order details and status.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each order item.
Identifier linking the order item to a specific customer order.
Identifier linking the order item to a specific product.
Quantity of the product ordered.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores details of each item in an order, linking orders to products and specifying quantities.
